---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
import CodeBlock from "../../components/CodeBlock.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="Package Manager" currentPath="/docs/packages">
  <h1>Package Manager (vslpkg)</h1>
  <p style="color:var(--c-text-secondary);font-size:var(--fs-md);margin-bottom:var(--s-6);">
    vslpkg is the Visuall package manager. Declare dependencies in <code>vsl.toml</code>,
    install with <code>vslpkg install</code>, and the compiler reads <code>vsl.lock</code>
    to resolve imports.
  </p>

  <h2>Package Store Layout</h2>
  <div style="overflow-x:auto;border:var(--border-width) solid var(--c-border);margin-bottom:var(--s-6);">
    <table style="border:none;">
      <thead><tr><th>Platform</th><th>Location</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Windows</td><td style="font-family:var(--font-mono);">%APPDATA%\visuall\packages\&lt;alias&gt;@&lt;version&gt;\</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Linux / macOS</td><td style="font-family:var(--font-mono);">~/.visuall/packages/&lt;alias&gt;@&lt;version&gt;/</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2>Creating a Package</h2>
  <CodeBlock
    code={`cd my-project
vslpkg init my-project`}
    lang="bash"
  />
  <p>This creates a <code>vsl.toml</code> scaffold:</p>
  <CodeBlock
    code={`[package]
name        = "my-project"   # lowercase letters, digits, hyphens
version     = "0.1.0"        # semver: MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH
description = ""
license     = ""             # SPDX identifier, e.g. "MIT"

[dependencies]
# alias = { git = "https://github.com/user/repo", version = "1.0.0" }
# alias = { path = "../local-lib" }`}
    lang="toml"
  />

  <h2>Declaring Dependencies</h2>
  <p>Two types of dependencies:</p>

  <h3>Git Dependency</h3>
  <p style="font-size:var(--fs-sm);color:var(--c-text-secondary);">
    Fetched from a remote Git repository at a specific tag (<code>v&lt;version&gt;</code>):
  </p>
  <CodeBlock
    code={`[dependencies]
mathlib = { git = "https://github.com/alice/mathlib", version = "1.0.0" }
utils   = { git = "https://github.com/bob/vsl-utils",  version = "2.3.1" }`}
    lang="toml"
  />

  <h3>Path Dependency</h3>
  <p style="font-size:var(--fs-sm);color:var(--c-text-secondary);">
    Points to a local directory with its own <code>vsl.toml</code>:
  </p>
  <CodeBlock
    code={`[dependencies]
mathlib = { path = "../mathlib" }
shared  = { path = "./vendor/shared" }`}
    lang="toml"
  />

  <h2>Installing Dependencies</h2>
  <CodeBlock code="vslpkg install" lang="bash" />
  <p style="font-size:var(--fs-sm);color:var(--c-text-secondary);">
    This resolves all transitive Git dependencies using <strong>Minimal Version Selection (MVS)</strong>,
    clones each into the local cache, and writes <code>vsl.lock</code>.
  </p>
  <p style="font-size:var(--fs-sm);color:var(--c-text-secondary);">
    To re-download and overwrite: <code>vslpkg install --force</code>
  </p>

  <h2>The Lockfile</h2>
  <p style="font-size:var(--fs-sm);color:var(--c-text-secondary);">
    After install, <code>vsl.lock</code> is written. Commit this to version control for reproducible builds.
  </p>
  <CodeBlock
    code={`# vsl.lock - generated by vslpkg - do not edit manually

[[package]]
alias   = "mathlib"
url     = "https://github.com/alice/mathlib"
version = "1.0.0"
dir     = "/home/alice/.visuall/packages/mathlib@1.0.0"

[[package]]
alias   = "utils"
dir     = "/home/alice/projects/vendor/utils"`}
    lang="toml"
  />

  <h2>Compiling with Packages</h2>
  <p style="font-size:var(--fs-sm);color:var(--c-text-secondary);">
    When <code>vsl.lock</code> exists in the same directory as your source (or its parent),
    <code>visuallc</code> loads it automatically. No extra flags needed:
  </p>
  <CodeBlock code="visuallc main.vsl -o main" lang="bash" />

  <h2>Publishing a Package</h2>
  <p style="font-size:var(--fs-sm);color:var(--c-text-secondary);">
    vslpkg fetches directly from Git. No central registry.
    To publish:
  </p>
  <ol>
    <li>Create a Git repo with your <code>.vsl</code> files and a <code>vsl.toml</code> at the root</li>
    <li>Tag a release: <code>git tag v1.0.0 &amp;&amp; git push origin v1.0.0</code></li>
    <li>Users add it to their <code>vsl.toml</code></li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Required Repository Layout</h3>
  <CodeBlock
    code={`mylib/
├── vsl.toml          # required: must be at the repository root
├── mylib.vsl         # your module source
└── ...`}
  />

  <h2>Versioning</h2>
  <div style="overflow-x:auto;border:var(--border-width) solid var(--c-border);margin-bottom:var(--s-6);">
    <table style="border:none;">
      <thead><tr><th>Change</th><th>Version bump</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Bug fix, no API change</td><td style="font-family:var(--font-mono);">PATCH (1.0.0 &rarr; 1.0.1)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>New backwards-compatible API</td><td style="font-family:var(--font-mono);">MINOR (1.0.0 &rarr; 1.1.0)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Breaking API change</td><td style="font-family:var(--font-mono);">MAJOR (1.0.0 &rarr; 2.0.0)</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
  <p style="font-size:var(--fs-sm);color:var(--c-text-secondary);">
    MVS selects the <strong>highest minimum</strong> version across all consumers, so breaking changes
    (major bumps) are not automatically adopted by dependents.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
